# Aurema Web Funnel — Project Overview

Aurema is a mindfulness / clarity app. This repository (`aurema-web`) hosts the marketing site and the **web growth-plan funnel** served at `aurema-app.com/growth-plan`.

The funnel drives new users through a short series of personalization steps and ends at a paywall. After paying, the user continues into the mobile app.

## Stack

- **Next.js 15** (App Router), **React 19**, **TypeScript**
- **Marketing pages**: Tailwind v4 + framer-motion (unchanged)
- **Funnel pages (`src/app/(funnel)/growth-plan/*`)**: **Chakra UI** (scoped)
- **Auth**: Firebase Auth (Google, Apple, email)
- **Payments**: RevenueCat Web Billing via `@revenuecat/purchases-js` (Stripe under the hood)
- **Analytics**: Amplitude (events + Amplitude Experiment for flags)
- **Email capture**: Brevo (already in deps)
- **Backend**: `aurema-backend` (Node/Express, Firebase Admin, existing RevenueCat webhook)

## Non-goals (do NOT add these without explicit ask)

- No monorepo / Turborepo split. Single Next app.
- No SSR variant allocation; experiments are client-side flags only.
- No direct Stripe SDK in our code — everything goes through RevenueCat.
- No multiple paywalls. One paywall page.
- No attribution / ad-platform integrations. Organic-first.
- No new auth providers beyond Google, Apple, email.

## Where things live

- `src/app/(funnel)/growth-plan/**` — funnel routes
- `src/funnel/**` — funnel domain code (steps, flow, state, components, services)
- `docs/funnel/**` — masterplan, architecture, runbooks, PROGRESS
- `.cursor/rules/**` — rules agents consume automatically
- `.cursor/skills/**` — step-by-step recipes for common tasks

Always read `docs/funnel/PROGRESS.md` first when starting work on the funnel.
